        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 19 at 3:30PM CDT until June 19 at 4:15PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>SVRLZK

The National Weather Service in Little Rock has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Pike County in southwestern Arkansas...
Southwestern Montgomery County in western Arkansas...

* Until 415 PM CDT.

* At 330 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Mimosa, or 12
miles west of Mount Ida, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Mount Ida...                      Norman...
Oden...                           Daisy...
Mimosa...                         Mauldin...
Daisy State Park...               Albert Pike Recreation Area...
Black Springs...                  Pencil Bluff...
Langley...                        Lodi...
Pine Ridge...                     Fancyhill...
Hopper...                         Caddo Gap...
Hurricane Grove...
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
